column8: 1. In a semester, how often have you felt upset due to something that happened in your academic affairs?
column9: 2. In a semester, how often you felt as if you were unable to control important things in your academic affairs?
column10: 3. In a semester, how often you felt nervous and stressed because of academic pressure?
column11: 4. In a semester, how often you felt as if you could not cope with all the mandatory academic activities? (e.g, assignments, quiz, exams)
column12: 5. In a semester, how often you felt confident about your ability to handle your academic / university problems?
column13: 6. In a semester, how often you felt as if things in your academic life is going on your way?
column14: 7. In a semester, how often are you able to control irritations in your academic / university affairs?
column15: 8. In a semester, how often you felt as if your academic performance was on top?
column16: 9. In a semester, how often you got angered due to bad performance or low grades that is beyond your control?
column17: 10. In a semester, how often you felt as if academic difficulties are piling up so high that you could not overcome them?
column18: 1. In a semester, how often you felt nervous, anxious or on edge due to academic pressure?
column19: 2. In a semester, how often have you been unable to stop worrying about your academic affairs?
column20: 3. In a semester, how often have you had trouble relaxing due to academic pressure?
column21: 4. In a semester, how often have you been easily annoyed or irritated because of academic pressure?
column22: 5. In a semester, how often have you worried too much about academic affairs?
column23: 6. In a semester, how often have you been so restless due to academic pressure that it is hard to sit still?
column24: 7. In a semester, how often have you felt afraid, as if something awful might happen?
column25: 1. In a semester, how often have you had little interest or pleasure in doing things?
column26: 2. In a semester, how often have you been feeling down, depressed or hopeless?
column27: 3. In a semester, how often have you had trouble falling or staying asleep, or sleeping too much?
column28: 4. In a semester, how often have you been feeling tired or having little energy?
column29: 5. In a semester, how often have you had poor appetite or overeating?
column30: 6. In a semester, how often have you been feeling bad about yourself - or that you are a failure or have let yourself or your family down?
column31: 7. In a semester, how often have you been having trouble concentrating on things, such as reading the books or watching television?
column32: 8. In a semester, how often have you moved or spoke too slowly for other people to notice? Or you've been moving a lot more than usual because you've been restless?
column33: 9. In a semester, how often have you had thoughts that you would be better off dead, or of hurting yourself?
